<div id='communityQuestionsWithAnswers'>
<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/1164400-after-reading-some-of-the-reviews-i-get">After reading some of the reviews I get the sense that The Child Finder has some element of the mystical. Does the book turn/depend upon the paranormal (past lives, alien abductions, third eyes, whatever)? Such components contribute to great fantasy novels, but not, in my opinion to &quot;mysteries.&quot; I was really annoyed by Behind Her Eyes and want to avoid another such reading experience.</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_1164400'><a id="like_count_community_question_1164400" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/1164400?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">6 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F33385438-the-child-finder">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/1164400-after-reading-some-of-the-reviews-i-get">4 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/1164400-after-reading-some-of-the-reviews-i-get">See all 13 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
